Xinhua commentary: turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization-Xinhuanet
Talent is the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talents?
Excellent migrant workers returning home are an indispensable new force.
Xinhua News Agency issued Hai Chunzuo
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26 th: Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in guoyuan, Meishan City, Sichuan Province. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands and returned to his hometown to start a business.
After several years of hard work, the annual income of the grape growing family farm he runs now exceeds one million yuan, and he has become a famous leader in getting rich, and has also been selected into the "two committees" of the village.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit farmers, such as poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong choose to return home to start businesses, which activates a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a province with a large population and a large labor export in western China, implemented the "excellent migrant workers' returning training project" according to the situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries, 61,000 village reserve forces and more than 20,000 party members were produced, which provided a strong guarantee for winning the tough fight against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
Well-off is not well-off, the key depends on fellow villagers.
Since the reform and opening-up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in rural China have gone out to work and increased their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
But objectively, it also leads to the rural hollowing out to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations. The village party branch secretaries and party members are characterized by "one old and one low", that is, aging, low academic qualifications, weak leaders of village party organizations, and outstanding problems.
If rural talents and other factors flow to cities all the time, and the countryside is in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is empty talk.
Attract those migrant workers who are capable, conscious and interested in serving their hometown, guide them to return home to start businesses and become rich leaders, and train them to become party members and rural cadres on the basis of merit, and enrich the ranks of grassroots cadres. This is the fundamental policy to solve the problem that the ranks of rural party members and grassroots party organizations are not connected with each other.
Excellent migrant workers are attracted back, but they must be retained and well done.
In recent years, Sichuan started from paying close attention to the party building of migrant workers, and established institutional mechanisms such as directional return, service guarantee, training and promotion, and selection and use of outstanding migrant workers on the basis of strict candidate criteria, so that they can improve their abilities, secure their jobs, have hope in their lives, truly take root in the countryside, and have a sense of accomplishment as entrepreneurs.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty, and talents are the key factor in the connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to this group of outstanding migrant workers returning home, and through comprehensive measures, turn them into a team and a new force that can stay, fight and take away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for the rural areas to get rid of poverty and run a well-off society and develop and revitalize.
