SealWu Wu Yifan, a well-known upmaster, also brought a "Wild Grass", which is a rap song adapted from Lu Xun's prose poems of the same name, and is very popular among young people.
Due to the epidemic situation, many graduates failed to experience the ritual feeling of picking ears and granting degree certificates on the spot, so they transferred the ritual feeling online.
According to the data, the peak popularity of live broadcast of this 2.5-hour concert exceeded 35 million.
"Follow your heart, seize the opportunity, don't care about the consequences, and sometimes you will have unexpected gains."
Although it is a graduation song party, many songs also move non-graduates.
