Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 26-Comprehensive Xinhua News Agency reporters abroad reported: On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Foreign Ministry informed the US Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the establishment and operation license of the US Consulate General in Chengdu, and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to stop all business and activities.
International public opinion holds that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious troubles to Sino-US relations, and it is justified and necessary for China to take countermeasures in response to the unreasonable provocation of the United States.
Andres Borchers, director of the Center for Chinese Studies at the Institute of International Studies of the University of Chile, said that the unilateral measures of the United States have destroyed the bridge of understanding between the Chinese and American peoples and brought the relations between the two major powers into crisis.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a counter-measure against the unilateral measures taken by the United States, which is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Giusto, a professor at the Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Arab-Chinese Research Center, believes that China's above-mentioned decision is a legitimate and necessary counter-measure against the previous provocation of the United States, not against ordinary Americans.
The United States tried to cover up its ineffective response to the COVID-19 outbreak by pressuring China, thus diverting the attention of the American people.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the provocative diplomatic attitude of the United States has caused serious troubles to Sino-US relations, and the relations between the two countries are facing severe challenges.
It is a normal counter-measure for China to inform the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu, which is in line with diplomatic practice. It not only reflects China's principled stand of resolutely safeguarding its own interests, but also reflects the rationality, advantages and restraint of China's diplomacy.
Francis Semwinza, a commentator on current affairs in Tanzania, said that China's above decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the provocation of the United States.
Sino-US relations should return to normal, and the US should take the initiative to improve relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve economic and political win-win with China, and how to benefit the two peoples and the whole international community.
Ali Yusuf, executive director of the Sudan-based Arab-Chinese Friendship Association Federation, said that China's forced counter-measures are a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the US side, in line with international law and the basic norms of international relations, and also in line with diplomatic practices.
Earlier, the United States demanded the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, which seriously violated international law and the basic norms of international relations.
It is hoped that the US side will rescind its previous decision and create the necessary conditions for the relations between the two countries to return to normal.
Singapore's Lianhe Zaobao published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to contain China and prevent China from continuing to rise.
In the face of the American pressure, although China is unwilling to see Sino-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
