(China's poverty reduction story) "blocking the south of the Yangtze River" pursues the poetic "Yellow River Dream"
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "The Jiuqu Yellow River has thousands of miles of sand, and the waves and winds are from the end of the world."
The Yellow River, which aroused the lofty sentiments of countless scholars, gave birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Nowadays, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "blocking the south of the Yangtze River", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
"Blue Wave Dream" with beautiful rivers and waters
"Ningxia, Huang Hefu", the Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers, which is the "mother river" for raising one side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes are out of balance, and chaos such as excessive sewage discharge, reclamation of land around lakes and encroachment on water areas are highlighted, resulting in black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting diversified restoration of water ecology, and striving to restore the Yellow River with beautiful water and clear river.
Water control should start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the method of "upgrading standard+pollution control+strict management", all industrial park sewage was treated centrally, all urban sewage treatment plants were discharged according to Grade A standard, and the black and odorous water bodies in urban built-up areas were basically eliminated, which successfully applied for the third batch of black and odorous water demonstration cities in China.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake length system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level responsibility system of river and lake length system in districts, cities, counties and villages, and it has become the norm for rivers and lakes to patrol rivers.
Gu Jincheng, 64, lives in a village near the Yellow River. He witnessed the changes of the Yellow River: "The water used to smell bad, and after remediation, the smell disappeared."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better, and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk along the Yellow River with his family to feel the clear water and blue sky.
"Wetland Dream" in Xiangji, Sha Ou
Birds, green trees, plank roads, clear water … Fan Zhongyan's beautiful scenery of "Sha Ou Xiangji" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming various wetlands along the way, such as river wetlands, lake wetlands and swamp wetlands, which play an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and water ecological balance, and at the same time become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan has a wetland area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%, with nearly 200 natural lakes and marshes, 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks and 8 municipal parks.
Lv Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, especially in birds. "The gull is an endangered bird, with only 20,000 in the world, of which Yinchuan Wetland is inhabited. More than 2,000."
At the same time, Ningxia has demarcated the red line of 500 meters in the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River according to law, which stipulates that no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the scope of protection except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Resources Service Center, said that through pollution source control, comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and terminal wetland construction, the water quality of nine main yellow drainage ditches in Ningxia has reached Class IV standard. "Now the water is clear, and the fish are also Swimming, the flowers are also blooming."
The "Drinking Water Dream" of Pu Huimin's Life
Yinchuan City, Ningxia once had an embarrassing title: the only city along the Yellow River that "guards the Yellow River and lacks water to drink".
Since 2010, Yinchuan has been facing the problem of persistent water shortage in the summer peak period. In recent ten years, "the pain of water shortage" has become a painful experience for many high-rise residents in summer. However, under the current situation that the major water sources are at the limit of over-exploitation and a large area of groundwater over-exploitation funnel area has been formed underground in the urban area, water shortage from water sources has become a difficult problem that puzzles Yinchuan.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good solution to the drinking problem of local residents.
Ming Ding, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Affairs Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia started the water supply project on the west line of urban and rural areas in Yinchuan metropolitan area in due course, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially passed through the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Suining Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River water."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water resources department will make overall plans to consider the transformation of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply integration. "Next, we will integrate all the scattered water supply points in rural areas and connect them to the west line water supply project. It is expected that the urban and rural areas in Yinchuan will be basically realized by the end of this year. Integrated water supply."
