Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporter Mao Siqian, Bai Yu) Encourage residents to do physical examinations frequently and find problems early; It is forbidden to sell alcoholic beverages to minors; Establish a health examination system for online games; Employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel ... Recently, the Health Regulations of Shenzhen Special Economic Zone (Draft for Soliciting Opinions) was officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "Health Law".
In order to encourage residents to take physical examinations frequently and find out problems as early as possible, the above-mentioned consultation draft proposes that health departments should make basic catalogues of physical examination items according to different ages, occupations and other factors.
Health examination expenses within the basic catalogue of health examination items shall be paid by the social medical insurance pooling fund according to the standard of once per person per year.
According to the draft for comment, the employer should rationally allocate human resources, arrange employees' work and rest time, and implement the rotation system for employees with heavy mental and physical labor load, so as to avoid excessive loss of human functions or physical and mental health damage to employees' health, and strictly implement the paid vacation system for employees.
In addition, the employer should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and organize regular physical examination of employees.
With regard to the physical and mental health of minors, the draft for consultation proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, and at the same time, the selling position of alcoholic beverages is restricted. Those who violate the regulations will be ordered by the market supervision and administration department to make corrections and be fined 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "prohibition of alcohol", minors should also "exercise more".
According to the requirements of the Exposure Draft, schools should arrange students' sports activities for more than one hour every day.
For online games, public security, culture, radio, television, tourism, sports, network supervision, health and other departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet service establishments, establish a health examination system for online games, and create a good communication space and culture for promoting the healthy growth of teenagers.
In addition, the Exposure Draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks when entering or leaving public places, and medical and health institutions should be fined 20,000 yuan for disclosing patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the Exposure Draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of public policy implementation on people's health before formulating plans and normative documents related to urban space planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization, ecological environment protection, and biomedical industry development, as well as approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
Without assessment or assessment will have a serious adverse impact on urban public health or residents' health, shall not be formulated or approved for implementation.
