The "Report on Savings after 90 Years" (2020 Edition) released by China New Economic Research Institute and Alipay recently shows that in the first half of the year, the "post-90 s" loved to save more: the per capita savings amount increased by nearly 40% compared with 2019.
Interestingly, the "post-90 s" tend to start with a small amount of money, and 60% of the average amount of money saved is below 20 yuan ...
Saving money with Yu 'ebao has also become the habit of saving money for the post-90s generation.
Data show that among the 700 million Yu 'ebao users, 134 million are "post-90s".
There are 174 million "post-90s" in China, that is to say, about three out of every four "post-90s" in China are saving money with Yu 'ebao.
At present, the 7-day annualized rate of return of money funds such as Yu 'ebao has dropped to about 1.5% from the level higher than 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it has not affected the pace of saving money for the post-90s generation.
Under the background of the "saving effect" of Yu 'ebao, many young people who are used to using Yu 'ebao are directly transformed into "basic people".
According to Alipay data, as of July 13th, the number of new "basic people" on Alipay has more than doubled in recent months, and more and more young people have realized "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the inflow of funds from Yu 'ebao into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of money funds in June.
The report also shows that "post-90 s" girls are more inclined to save money, with an average of 20% higher than boys' money; Among the users who hold funds on Alipay platform, 60% are men, and women tend to choose more stable financial management methods than men.
After saving money, what are the plans for the post-90s generation?
According to Alipay data, "post-90s generation" have the habit of saving money for their goals, and most users take travel as their goal of saving money.
Affected by the epidemic, many "post-90 s" saved money to prepare for travel after the epidemic; The reopening of cinemas also provides a new way to change from saving money to spending.
