French Defense Minister Floran Paley said on the 24th that France will add hundreds of millions of euros to its space defense budget and develop its space military force to prevent other countries from taking "unfriendly actions" in outer space.
On the same day, Paley told Provence that from 2019 to 2025, the expenditure budget of French space military projects will increase from 3.6 billion euros (about 4.2 billion dollars) to 4.3 billion euros (5 billion dollars).
According to the French Military Planning Act 2019-2025 approved by the French Parliament in 2018, France is expected to update the existing observation satellites and communication satellites and launch three electromagnetic interception satellites to improve the modernization level of space surveillance radar.
French President Emmanuel Macron announced in July last year that a space military command and an "aviation and space force" would be set up within the French Air Force.
Pali said that she will officially announce the establishment of this space force when she visits a military academy in Salon, Provence.
Paley said that this space force belongs to the Air Force and will have 500 personnel by 2025.
She said: "People used to think that space served the common interests of science, but this idea is gone forever. Today, space is a place where countries compete for global hegemony. "
Pali reiterated Macron's previous statement that France has no intention of provoking an arms race.
"We are by no means engaged in an arms race. But I have the responsibility to thoroughly recognize the threats we may face. "
Paley revisited the surveillance of a military satellite shared by France and Italy in 2017.
She said that "peeping" was a Russian satellite.
Russia denies this claim.
Paley said that France "will soon" have a small patrol satellite capable of detecting and targeting "those black hands behind unfriendly actions".
According to French media, the reason why France seeks to establish a space force is that US President Donald Trump asked the US Department of Defense to draft a bill to establish a space force in February last year.
Trump signed the National Defense Authorization Act in December last year, approving the establishment of the sixth largest US military service, the Space Force.
Some experts are worried that these measures by the United States have accelerated the pace of militarization of American space and may trigger a new round of space arms race.
