(Reporter Yang Zhaokui) "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") released by the National Information Center Sharing Economy Research Center recently shows that due to the impact of the epidemic, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market decreased by 72.1% year on year in the first five months of 2020.
However, the shared accommodation market has been warming up since March, and the market turnover, order volume and reception number have gradually recovered.
According to the "Report", the transaction volume of the shared accommodation market has dropped sharply. On the one hand, the demand for travel accommodation has dropped sharply under the prevention and control of the epidemic, and the order volume has dropped sharply. The total order volume in the first five months decreased by 65% year-on-year, and the number of receptions decreased by 63% year-on-year; On the other hand, the weak demand also led to a more obvious drop in overnight prices, with the average overnight prices in the first five months dropping by 16% year-on-year.
However, the market transaction volume in March, April and May increased by 78%, 199% and 35% respectively; The number of orders increased by 141%, 152% and 50% respectively; The number of visitors increased by 81%, 112% and 28% respectively.
The "Report" pointed out that the development of shared accommodation industry is promising for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economic Research Center of the National Information Center, told the Workers Daily that the development of shared accommodation requires stronger policy support. On the one hand, it is necessary to implement the policies that have been introduced in the early stage, further strengthen policy publicity and focus on creating a better business environment; On the other hand, it is necessary to further increase policy guidance and support from stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourism accommodation services, innovating service methods and strengthening cooperation between the government and platform enterprises.
