The longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area runs through-Zhongxin.com
2020-07-26 17:34:48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo courtesy of China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Corporation
Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on July 26 that the Zheng Wan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers, was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed railway tunnel with a design speed of 350 km/h among the projects currently under construction in China.
Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway is located in Henan, Hubei and Chongqing, connecting Beijing-Guangzhou high-speed railway and Xulan high-speed railway in the north of Zhengzhou, and connecting Chongqing-Wanzhou high-speed railway to Chongqing in the south of Wanzhou. It is an important part of the Yangtze River Passage and Hunan Passage in China's "eight vertical and eight horizontal" high-speed railway network.
Zhengwan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows running through the site.
Zhengwan high-speed railway starts from Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and goes southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City and Xiangyang City, Hubei Province to Wanzhou District, Chongqing. The newly-built line is about 818 kilometers long, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section has been put into operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which runs through the whole line on 26th, is a control project of Zhengwan High-speed Railway. The project is located at the junction of fengjie county and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017, and the whole tunnel was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, the person in charge of the design of Zhengwan High-speed Railway Tunnel of China Railway Second Institute Engineering Group Co., Ltd., which is the survey and design party, the topographic and geological conditions of the small Three Gorges Tunnel are very complex, facing the risks of karst, sudden mud gushing, large deformation of soft rock, etc. It is a Class I high-risk tunnel, and the design and construction of the tunnel are extremely difficult.
"In the process of project construction, we used geological survey method, geophysical prospecting method and advanced drilling method to make advance geological forecast, and adopted special design schemes for more than 30 karst caves of various types. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was designed and built, crossing a large cave with a longitudinal length of over 10 meters and a depth of over 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement. " Wang Guojun said.
According to the introduction of the construction party, China Railway Tunnel Bureau, when the tunnel was constructed, the combination of dredging and blocking was adopted. By building horizontal tunnel guide, grouting and blocking water, strengthening tunnel structural support and building sewage treatment station, the orderly progress of the project was ensured, and the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Small Three Gorges Scenic Area was avoided. At the same time, the construction problems such as bad geology such as large deformation of soft rock with a length of 7 kilometers, and water inrush from multiple mud with a daily maximum water inflow of 157,000 cubic meters were successfully overcome.
After the entire Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway line is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger transport main channel from Southwest China to Central Plains, North China and Northeast China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the northeast railway channel in Southwest China, improve the layout of regional road network, speed up the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the line, promote regional coordinated development, and promote the implementation of the western development strategy.
