The overall stability of employment and prices shows that the economy has "temperature"
Economic Daily China Economic Net reporter Lin Huocan
In the first half of this year, facing the impact of the Covid-19 epidemic, China made overall plans to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The situation of epidemic prevention and control kept improving, and the steady economic recovery was obvious. The employment and price performance closely related to people's livelihood were generally stable, and the Chinese economy handed over a transcript of economic operation with temperature.
In the first two months of this year, the surveyed unemployment rate increased.
Especially in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically in a state of suspension of production, the employment demand of enterprises decreased, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the unemployment rate in urban survey increased.
With the gradual improvement of epidemic prevention and control situation, the production and living order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The CPC Central Committee adheres to the general tone of striving for stability, further intensifies the macro-policy opposition, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the work of aiding enterprises to stabilize posts and expand employment.
China has stepped up policies to hedge and stabilize jobs, playing a combination of "reduction and exemption, slow return and subsidy" policies, reducing and exempting three social insurance unit contributions in stages, allowing deferred payment of social insurance premiums, expanding the benefits of stable post return of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized enterprises, and replacing training with workers, and providing absorption subsidies and probation subsidies for enterprises to absorb employment of key groups.
With the implementation of various policies to stabilize employment, the employment demand of enterprises has steadily rebounded, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns has gradually declined. In June, the surveyed unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Department of Population and Employment Statistics of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to take effect, and the labor force who quit due to the epidemic situation in the early stage returned one after another. The urban labor participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February, which was close to the same level last year.
The data shows that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; The average weekly working hours of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, 6.6 hours higher than that in February and 0.1 hour higher than that in January.
Prices are also related to thousands of families.
In January this year, CPI rose by 5.4% year on year, setting a new high for many years.
In February, the year-on-year increase of CPI declined slightly, but it was still in the "5 range".
The year-on-year increase of CPI is at a high level, which is caused by the consumption demand before the Spring Festival, the wrong month of the Spring Festival and the low year-on-year base.
However, the impact of the Covid-19 epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by epidemic prevention and control, logistics delay, untimely material supply and increased material transportation cost occurred all over the country in January and February. In addition, some citizens hoarded and snapped up, and the prices of some daily necessities increased significantly.
In order to cope with the disturbance of price situation caused by epidemic prevention and control, relevant departments have brought important living materials into the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure smooth transportation of materials.
Under the action of a series of policy measures, the market supply of vegetables and fruits has been strongly guaranteed.
In response to the rapid increase in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government issued the policy of ensuring supply and stabilizing prices, all regions and departments quickly implemented it, and the pork reserve supply was significantly improved, the pig production capacity was restored in an orderly manner, and the production and marketing order gradually became normal.
Since March, pork prices have continued to decline, and in May, the year-on-year increase in food prices has dropped back to 10.6%; In June, pork prices rose slightly month on month due to factors such as the slow release of live pigs, the decrease in imports and the rebound in group consumption demand.
Seasonal changes of fresh vegetable prices are obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high base of comparison in the same period last year, the price of fresh fruits continued to decline year on year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the masses has been effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation has remained stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, all localities have increased their efforts to ensure supply, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Since March, the CPI has declined for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase has also dropped from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the overall price level has returned to a stable level.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level, and the overall inflationary pressure is not great, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and living order on the premise of normalization of epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively deal with natural disasters such as floods and droughts in the main producing areas of agricultural products such as grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on hoarding, price gouging and other behaviors that disrupt market order.
