According to the announcement, in order to further deepen the reform of state-owned and state-owned enterprises, optimize the adjustment of the layout structure of state-owned assets, and improve the shareholding structure of Greenland, Shanghai Real Estate (Group) Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as "Shanghai Real Estate") and Shanghai Chengtou (Group) Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as "Shanghai Chengtou") intend to transfer part of the shares held by the company through public solicitation of transferees, and the total proportion of shares to be transferred shall not exceed 17.5% of the total share capital of Greenland.
The price of the shares to be transferred this time is not lower than the higher of the following two: the arithmetic average of the daily weighted average price of the first 30 trading days before the announcement date (July 27, 2020); The audited net asset value per share of the company in the latest fiscal year.
