Since its establishment, Greenland Holdings has carried out many institutional reforms: from 1992 to 1997, it operated according to market-oriented rules under the pure state-owned system; From 1997 to 2013, establish and continuously improve the shareholding system of state-owned holding and employee stock ownership; From 2013 to 2015, strategic investors were introduced to form a mixed ownership system with cross-shareholding and mutual integration of state-owned and non-public capital; Since 2015, it has been listed as a public company.
Greenland's current mixed reform scheme is similar to Gree's. In December 2019, Zhuhai Mingjun led by Gao Yan Capital took over 15% equity of Gree Electric Appliances (000651. SZ) with RMB 41.662 billion, and Gree Group retired as a minority shareholder. After completing the mixed reform, Gree Electric Appliances implemented modern enterprise management methods such as executive incentive plan and no real controller structure.
