Dina Town used to be a poor township with "covering the valley and potatoes for the spring and autumn". Ten years ago, the incidence of local poverty was as high as 25.8%.
It is extremely urgent to change the traditional planting habits, adjust the industrial structure and increase farmers' income in the critical period of getting rid of poverty and getting into decisive battle.
After many visits, Chen Chao, secretary of the Party Committee of Yina Town, and a group of people in the town thought that industrial development could no longer follow the old path.
Therefore, Yina Town introduced leading enterprises and planted apples in a modern way.
Hou Jianwen, deputy general manager of Weining Beyond Agriculture Co., Ltd., came to Yina Town from Shaanxi in 2015 for investigation, took a fancy to the local planting conditions at a glance, and planted apple trees locally from 2016.
At first, the village mobilized Li Yuanzhong to transfer the land to plant apple trees. Li Yuanzhong and his wife made a mistake in their hearts: "I have planted apples for so many years, and I have not seen who planted apples in the village to make a fortune."
"The apples planted are dwarf apples, which will not make the apple trees grow too high."
What Li Yuanzhong didn't expect was that this apple planting adopted a new method. Irrigation pipes were laid under each apple tree, and water and fertilizer were poured to the roots. When harvesting fruit in autumn, the tractor drove directly into the orchard, and the fruit could be picked when standing.
At present, the apple base has gradually entered a high-yield period, and the market is just as expected by Hou Jianwen. Apples are not to be sold, and are deeply loved by consumers in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and other cities.
The growing apple industry has brought new changes to Li Yuanzhong's life. Although farming is still in progress, there is a new source of income.
Li Yuanzhong's family has transferred more than 9 mu of land to the Apple Base. Every year, in addition to the guaranteed land transfer fee, there is also a profit dividend after hanging fruit. The couple usually work in the base. "One person can get 80 yuan every day and have a job all the year round".
Li Yuanzhong told reporters that last year's profit dividend was more than 2,800 yuan, plus the land transfer fee and the couple's income from working, and the family earned more than 80,000 yuan. "There is no need for food and clothing, and the well-off life has already passed.".
"At present, it has achieved initial results. The annual output value of 1 mu of apples exceeds 15,000 yuan, which is about 10 times that of corn."
Chen Chao told reporters that 20,000 mu of apples have been planted in the whole town of Yina, with 6,000 mu in Zhonghai Village alone, covering 4,056 households and 17,200 people, including 656 households and 2,952 poor households who set up files and set up cards. The annual salary is more than 6 million yuan, which really realizes that the base is built at the door of the house and there is no need to go out to work.
Li Yuanzhong, whose pockets are bulging day by day, has also begun to realize his "wish".
During the Lunar New Year this year, Li Yuanzhong bought an off-road vehicle. Now he drives to and from work every day. "There are still more than ten acres of land at home. When the next step is to expand the scale of the Apple base, all of them will be transferred to them, and the income will be even more."
