Large-scale media action "Going to the village to see poverty alleviation"-Today's news-Hunan Daily News-Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily, New Hunan Client, July 25 (Reporter) On July 25, the large-scale media action "Going to the Village to Live and See Poverty Alleviation" sponsored by the Financial and Economic Program Center of the Central Radio and Television General Station started from Xuzhou, Jiangsu Province, and two caravans carrying 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system slowly drove out of the scene after being watched by the on-site guests.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that "2020 is a milestone year, we will build a well-off society in an all-round way and achieve the goal of the first century, and 2020 will also be the year of decisive battle against poverty".
The large-scale media action "Going to the Village to Live and See Poverty Alleviation" is an important measure for the Financial and Economic Program Center of the Central Radio and Television General Station to do a good job in poverty alleviation propaganda to match this major theme.
This action will go into poverty-stricken villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government, dig fresh stories of poverty alleviation, directly attack the great changes in the appearance of villages, and show the course of how villagers break through the predicament of survival and development and move towards the road of becoming rich.
The operation will last for more than three months.
The reporter started from Xuzhou, and the soldiers were divided into two roads, all the way to the southwest line, passing through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet and other places; The other one takes the northwest line, passing through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Hebei and other places, with a journey of more than 10,000 kilometers.
In the form of reporting, "Going to the Village to Watch Poverty Alleviation" is boldly integrated.
The economic development of the villages where the caravans go will be broadcast through CCTV Financial Channel, Voice of Yangguang Economy, China Traffic Radio and CCTV Financial New Media.
Among them, the live TV broadcast will be mainly completed in the midday news program Tianxia Finance of CCTV Financial Channel (premiere time: 12: 00-13: 00 from Monday to Sunday), and the prime news column "Economic Information Network" of CCTV Financial Channel will set up a report column on poverty alleviation (premiere time: 20: 30-21: 30 from Monday to Sunday).
At the same time, the caravan will broadcast live for up to one hour on the CCTV financial client, and the audience can watch the live broadcast and participate in the lottery by downloading the CCTV financial APP.
In terms of technology application and studio design, "Going to the Village to Watch Poverty Alleviation" made a breakthrough and pioneered the "New Media Caravan in Outfield".
The car is equipped with 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system, and uses 5G+4K/8K+AI technology to realize the organic combination of online and offline, big screen and small screen, and TV broadcasting.
Three-news broadcasting area is equipped, which is converted from containers, with a length of 12m, a width of 2.55m and a height of 3.98m. The box adopts hydraulic automatic unfolding structure, which can be turned up to 120 degrees at the maximum.
The studio area can also be unfolded automatically, and is externally connected with the expansion platform, covering an area of more than 50 square meters, which can meet the scene requirements of most sub-projects.
At present, Dongchuan District of Kunming is already hot in summer, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation site.
Ling Lv, an employee of Kunming Aisifu Electronic Technology Co., Ltd. said, "Now, as soon as you leave your home, you will enter the factory door to make money and take care of your family. Thanks to the free vocational skills training organized by the trade union."
Walking into the poverty alleviation workshop of electronic components processing in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a busy picture with great enthusiasm came into view.
Ling Lv, who is in her forties, is a single mother, who takes care of her children and her elderly parents.
When she was in the most difficult time, Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions helped to give advice and find a way to "get help in the snow".
Since 2018, Lv Ling has received assistance policies such as housing, schooling, social security and employment, as well as assistance payments from trade unions at all levels.
This year, her children have successfully graduated and got employment, and she herself got a job and income after taking part in skills training, and got out of trouble at the end of April.
It is reported that Dongchuan District has organized a special skill training program to help overcome poverty, which is part of the skill training work of Yunnan Federation of Trade Unions.
According to the characteristics of the employees in difficulty in the relocation and resettlement sites for poverty alleviation in the district, the district general manager made an in-depth investigation to understand the training needs, determined the training types, and planned to train 450 electricians, welders and pastry chefs in the near future.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of Menglian County Branch of Agricultural Bank of Yunnan, wrote a sincere thank-you letter to the County Federation of Trade Unions.
In her letter, she sincerely thanked the trade union for giving her the Golden Autumn Student Aid from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the files of employees in difficulty. Since then, she has been enjoying the care of the policy of setting up files and establishing cards.
With the help of local trade unions, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been lifted out of poverty through institutional guarantee and precise assistance.
The success of Lv Ling's family and Li Yi in getting rid of difficulties is a microcosm of Yunnan trade unions' efforts to promote the relief of difficult workers.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Rights Protection Work Department of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions, the provincial government has strengthened the dynamic management of the files of difficult employees, promoted the normalization of the filing work, and timely incorporated the difficult employees who meet the filing conditions into the assistance system; Broaden the application channels for employees with difficulties, and use WeChat to open an online filing service platform for employees with difficulties, so as to facilitate employees with difficulties to declare on their own initiative in a timely manner.
During the epidemic period, it was difficult to go out to work. In order to help the employees with difficulties in file to relieve their living pressure, Yunnan Province has arranged more than 13 million yuan of send warm funds to carry out special send warm condolence activities for more than 6,000 national and 1,000 provincial employees with difficulties in file according to the national and provincial standards of 2,000 yuan per household.
At the same time, the provincial general manager connects with various internet recruitment platforms such as human and social departments and Zhaopin recruitment, pushes recruitment information to employees in difficulty, and provides employment consulting and employment guidance services.
